<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>go into business • go to business</xh5><p> <i>go into business—</i>engage in production or commerce: ...it was better to sell sock-suspenders in Honolulu than to play small parts in Cleveland, Ohio. He left the stage and <u>went into the business</u>.</p><p> <i>go to business—</i>1. go to one’s office: “When I <u>go to business</u> tomorrow, I will just have a look at Mr. Fitz’s account,” Mr. Rowdy thought. 2. <i>(also: come to business)</i> discuss the basic and most important facts or realities of smth.: Finns are not very talkative and they like to <u>go straight to business</u>, when it comes to negotiations.</p> </entry>
